{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015FeKA3wRknjauUZwDH8A48","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Scout Report — Cycle 106\n2\t\n3\t**Date:** 2026-05-25  \n4\t**Cycle:** 106  \n5\t**Mode:** full (no goal; broad discovery)  \n6\t**Strategy:** balanced  \n7\t**Branch:** main — last commit `05ee503`\n8\t\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\t## Discovery Summary\n12\t\n13\tv12.1.0 shipped clean (3 capabilities: plan-mode dispatch, arbitrary phase compose, auto-pick interactive policy). Three issues surfaced post-release:\n14\t\n15\t1. **Uncommitted critical bug fixes** in `bridge.go` and `runner.go` — fix ExtraFlags pass-through breakage and \"auto\" model sentinel rejection by claude -p.\n16\t2. **Runtime artifacts tracked by git** — `go/.evolve/guards.log` and `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` were committed; they should be gitignored runtime files.\n17\t3. **Missing happy-path test** — runner tests achieve 100% statement coverage for auto-model resolution but never exercise the `resolvellm.Resolve` success path.\n18\t\n19\t**System health:** All 39 packages pass. Bridge: 97.8% coverage. Runner: 100% statement coverage (branch gap noted above).\n20\t\n21\t---\n22\t\n23\t## Key Findings\n24\t\n25\t| # | Finding | Severity |\n26\t|---|---------|----------|\n27\t| 1 | `bridge.go` ExtraFlags `--` separator uncommitted; `--permission-mode` fails without it | HIGH |\n28\t| 2 | `runner.go` auto-model sentinel resolution uncommitted; \"auto\" reaches claude -p → HTTP 404 | HIGH |\n29\t| 3 | `go/.evolve/guards.log` + `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` tracked by git (runtime artifacts) | MEDIUM |\n30\t| 4 | Runner test never exercises happy-path: resolvellm returns a model and replaces \"auto\" | MEDIUM |\n31\t\n32\t---\n33\t\n34\t## Research\n35\t\n36\t**KB search results:** `knowledge-base/research/` — no prior dossier on bridge flag pass-through patterns.\n37\t\n38\t**Inline findings:**\n39\t- Bridge `bin/bridge` uses `--) shift; break ;;` POSIX pass-through: inserting `--` before ExtraFlags is the structural fix, not an allowlist expansion.\n40\t- `resolvellm.Options` exposes `Env`, `ConfigPath`, `ProjectRoot` seams for testing — can inject a mock config path in runner tests without changing production code.\n41\t- `go/.evolve/` under a subdirectory is not matched by root `.gitignore` rule `.evolve/*` (that only matches root-level `.evolve/`). Need `**/.evolve/` or per-directory `.gitignore`.\n42\t\n43\t---\n44\t\n45\t## Research → Implementation Map\n46\t\n47\t| Finding | Implementation |\n48\t|---------|----------------|\n49\t| Bridge ExtraFlags separator | Commit `bridge.go` + `bridge_test.go` as-is, rebuild binary |\n50\t| Auto-model sentinel | Commit `runner.go` as-is; add seam for happy-path test |\n51\t| Tracked runtime logs | `git rm --cached`, add `**/.evolve/` to `.gitignore` |\n52\t| Missing happy-path test | Inject fake `llm_config.json` via `resolvellm.Options.ConfigPath` seam in runner_test.go |\n53\t\n54\t---\n55\t\n56\t## Hypotheses\n57\t\n58\t1. **H1 (standard):** Without the `--` separator, every cycle using `EVOLVE_BUILD_PERMISSION_MODE=plan` silently falls back to default-mode because bridge aborts on \"unknown flag\" — the v12.1.0 Capability 1 feature is effectively broken for all users with permission-mode enabled.\n59\t\n60\t2. **H2 (standard):** The tracked `guards.log` files will accumulate noise diffs every cycle, causing confusing git status output and making it harder to detect real uncommitted changes.\n61\t\n62\t3. **H3 (beyond-ask):** The auto-model resolution gap means any operator who sets `DefaultModel()` to return `\"auto\"` (the intended production posture for phase hooks) gets a hard 404 from the API. This is a silent regression introduced by adding the `resolvellm` wire without a proper seam in the runner interface.\n63\t\n64\t---\n65\t\n66\t## Beyond-the-Ask Hypotheses\n67\t\n68\t- **BTA-1:** The root cause of the tracked `guards.log` problem is that `evolve` was run from `go/` and `go/cmd/evolve/` directories during development — the binary discovers the project root relative to CWD, not its own path. The stale `go/.evolve/cycle-state.json` also caused role-gate enforcement against a phantom cycle-1, blocking scout writes to cycle-106 workspace. Anchoring `.evolve/` to `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` would prevent all future stray artifacts.\n69\t\n70\t---\n71\t\n72\t## Selected Tasks\n73\t\n74\t### Task 1: Commit and ship bug fixes as v12.1.1 patch [S]\n75\t\n76\t**What:** Commit `bridge.go`, `bridge_test.go`, `runner.go` (already modified, all tests passing), rebuild `go/evolve` binary, run release pipeline for v12.1.1.\n77\t\n78\t**Target files:**\n79\t- `go/internal/adapters/bridge/bridge.go` (ExtraFlags `--` separator)\n80\t- `go/internal/adapters/bridge/bridge_test.go` (2 new tests for separator behavior)\n81\t- `go/internal/phases/runner/runner.go` (auto-model sentinel resolution)\n82\t- `go/evolve` (binary rebuild)\n83\t- `CHANGELOG.md`, version files (via release pipeline)\n84\t\n85\t**Complexity:** S | **Effort:** 3 turns  \n86\t**Evidence:** `git diff HEAD` shows exact changes; all tests green (bridge 97.8%, runner 100%).\n87\t\n88\t**Acceptance criteria:**\n89\t- `git diff HEAD` shows no modified files in bridge or runner packages\n90\t- `go test ./...` all pass\n91\t- `./go/evolve --version` reports v12.1.1\n92\t- `bash legacy/scripts/utility/release.sh` exits 0\n93\t\n94\t**Recommended skills:** `evolve-loop:evolve-ship`, `go-build`\n95\t\n96\t---\n97\t\n98\t### Task 2: Untrack runtime artifacts + fix gitignore for go/.evolve/ [S]\n99\t\n100\t**What:** Untrack `go/.evolve/guards.log` and `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` via `git rm --cached`, add glob rule to `.gitignore` so subdirectory `.evolve/` dirs are excluded.\n101\t\n102\t**Target files:**\n103\t- `.gitignore` (add `go/.evolve/` and `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/` rules, or `**/.evolve/` glob)\n104\t\n105\t**Complexity:** S | **Effort:** 2 turns  \n106\t**Evidence:** 