tturns_used: 9\n256\t```\n257\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"715c7e05-5ffe-4c3b-8250-1e3ef685eb10","uuid":"125f6cad-3bf9-44ae-a049-e08a9d280873","timestamp":"2026-05-25T06:40:00.066Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"~/ai/claude/evolve-loop/.evolve/runs/cycle-106/workspace/scout-report.md","content":"# Scout Report — Cycle 106\n\n**Date:** 2026-05-25  \n**Cycle:** 106  \n**Mode:** full (no goal; broad discovery)  \n**Strategy:** balanced  \n**Branch:** main — last commit `05ee503`\n\n---\n\n## Discovery Summary\n\nv12.1.0 shipped clean (3 capabilities: plan-mode dispatch, arbitrary phase compose, auto-pick interactive policy). Three issues surfaced post-release:\n\n1. **Uncommitted critical bug fixes** in `bridge.go` and `runner.go` — fix ExtraFlags pass-through breakage and \"auto\" model sentinel rejection by claude -p.\n2. **Runtime artifacts tracked by git** — `go/.evolve/guards.log` and `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` were committed; they should be gitignored runtime files.\n3. **Missing happy-path test** — runner tests achieve 100% statement coverage for auto-model resolution but never exercise the `resolvellm.Resolve` success path.\n\n**System health:** All 39 packages pass. Bridge: 97.8% coverage. Runner: 100% statement coverage (branch gap noted above).\n\n---\n\n## Key Findings\n\n| # | Finding | Severity |\n|---|---------|----------|\n| 1 | `bridge.go` ExtraFlags `--` separator uncommitted; `--permission-mode` fails without it | HIGH |\n| 2 | `runner.go` auto-model sentinel resolution uncommitted; \"auto\" reaches claude -p → HTTP 404 | HIGH |\n| 3 | `go/.evolve/guards.log` + `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` tracked by git (runtime artifacts) | MEDIUM |\n| 4 | Runner test never exercises happy-path: resolvellm returns a model and replaces \"auto\" | MEDIUM |\n\n---\n\n## Research\n\n**KB search results:** `knowledge-base/research/` — no prior dossier on bridge flag pass-through patterns.\n\n**Inline findings:**\n- Bridge `bin/bridge` uses `--) shift; break ;;` POSIX pass-through: inserting `--` before ExtraFlags is the structural fix, not an allowlist expansion.\n- `resolvellm.Options` exposes `Env`, `ConfigPath`, `ProjectRoot` seams for testing — can inject a mock config path in runner tests without changing production code.\n- `go/.evolve/` under a subdirectory is not matched by root `.gitignore` rule `.evolve/*` (that only matches root-level `.evolve/`). Need `**/.evolve/` or per-directory `.gitignore`.\n\n---\n\n## Research → Implementation Map\n\n| Finding | Implementation |\n|---------|----------------|\n| Bridge ExtraFlags separator | Commit `bridge.go` + `bridge_test.go` as-is, rebuild binary |\n| Auto-model sentinel | Commit `runner.go` as-is; add seam for happy-path test |\n| Tracked runtime logs | `git rm --cached`, add `**/.evolve/` to `.gitignore` |\n| Missing happy-path test | Inject fake `llm_config.json` via `resolvellm.Options.ConfigPath` seam in runner_test.go |\n\n---\n\n## Hypotheses\n\n1. **H1 (standard):** Without the `--` separator, every cycle using `EVOLVE_BUILD_PERMISSION_MODE=plan` silently falls back to default-mode because bridge aborts on \"unknown flag\" — the v12.1.0 Capability 1 feature is effectively broken for all users with permission-mode enabled.\n\n2. **H2 (standard):** The tracked `guards.log` files will accumulate noise diffs every cycle, causing confusing git status output and making it harder to detect real uncommitted changes.\n\n3. **H3 (beyond-ask):** The auto-model resolution gap means any operator who sets `DefaultModel()` to return `\"auto\"` (the intended production posture for phase hooks) gets a hard 404 from the API. This is a silent regression introduced by adding the `resolvellm` wire without a proper seam in the runner interface.\n\n---\n\n## Beyond-the-Ask Hypotheses\n\n- **BTA-1:** The root cause of the tracked `guards.log` problem is that `evolve` was run from `go/` and `go/cmd/evolve/` directories during development — the binary discovers the project root relative to CWD, not its own path. The stale `go/.evolve/cycle-state.json` also caused role-gate enforcement against a phantom cycle-1, blocking scout writes to cycle-106 workspace. Anchoring `.evolve/` to `git rev-parse --show-toplevel` would prevent all future stray artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## Selected Tasks\n\n### Task 1: Commit and ship bug fixes as v12.1.1 patch [S]\n\n**What:** Commit `bridge.go`, `bridge_test.go`, `runner.go` (already modified, all tests passing), rebuild `go/evolve` binary, run release pipeline for v12.1.1.\n\n**Target files:**\n- `go/internal/adapters/bridge/bridge.go` (ExtraFlags `--` separator)\n- `go/internal/adapters/bridge/bridge_test.go` (2 new tests for separator behavior)\n- `go/internal/phases/runner/runner.go` (auto-model sentinel resolution)\n- `go/evolve` (binary rebuild)\n- `CHANGELOG.md`, version files (via release pipeline)\n\n**Complexity:** S | **Effort:** 3 turns  \n**Evidence:** `git diff HEAD` shows exact changes; all tests green (bridge 97.8%, runner 100%).\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- `git diff HEAD` shows no modified files in bridge or runner packages\n- `go test ./...` all pass\n- `./go/evolve --version` reports v12.1.1\n- `bash legacy/scripts/utility/release.sh` exits 0\n\n**Recommended skills:** `evolve-loop:evolve-ship`, `go-build`\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Untrack runtime artifacts + fix gitignore for go/.evolve/ [S]\n\n**What:** Untrack `go/.evolve/guards.log` and `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` via `git rm --cached`, add glob rule to `.gitignore` so subdirectory `.evolve/` dirs are excluded.\n\n**Target files:**\n- `.gitignore` (add `go/.evolve/` and `go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/` rules, or `**/.evolve/` glob)\n\n**Complexity:** S | **Effort:** 2 turns  \n**Evidence:** `git status` shows `M go/.evolve/guards.log` and `M go/cmd/evolve/.evolve/guards.log` as tracked modified files; caused role-gate phantom enforcement.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- `git ls-files go/.evolve/` returns empty\n- `git status` shows neither file as tracked\n- Running `./go/evolve --help` from project root does not create new tracked files\n\n**Recommended skills:** `git-workflow`\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Add runner seam + happy-path test for auto-model sentinel resolution [S]\n\n**What:** Add `ResolverOpts resolvellm.Options` field to `runner.Options`, pass it through to `resolvellm.Resolve` call in runner.go, add test `TestRun_AutoModel_ResolvesViaLLMConfig` that writes a minimal `llm_config.json` to a temp dir and asserts bridge receives a concrete model name.\n\n**Target files:**\n- `go/internal/phases/runner/runner.go` (add `ResolverOpts` field to `Options`)\n- `go/internal/phases/runner/runner_test.go` (new test with ConfigPath seam)\n\n**Complexity:** S | **Effort:** 3 turns  \n**Evidence:** `resolvellm.Options.ConfigPath` seam exists; current tests always hit error path in temp dir.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- New test `TestRun_AutoModel_ResolvesViaLLMConfig` PASS\n- `go test -cover github.com/mickeyyaya/evolveloop/go/internal/phases/runner` ≥ 100%\n- Bridge receives `Model != \"auto\"` in the happy-path test\n\n**Recommended skills:** `go-review`, `tdd`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n\n| Task | Key Check |\n|------|-----------|\n| T1: Ship v12.1.1 | All tests green + `evolve --version` = v12.1.1 + release.sh exits 0 |\n| T2: Untrack artifacts | `git ls-files go/.evolve/` empty + no new tracked files after run |\n| T3: Auto-model test | New test PASS + bridge.Model != \"auto\" in happy path |\n\n---\n\n## Carryover Decisions\n\n*No carryover todos — state.json:carryoverTodos is empty.*\n\n---\n\n## Deferred\n\nNone.\n\n---\n\n## Research Cache\n\n| Task | Cache status |\n|------|-------------|\n| T1 (bridge ExtraFlags fix) | NO_ENTRY — first cycle addressing this fix |\n| T2 (gitignore for go/.evolve/) | NO_ENTRY — new discovery |\n| T3 (auto-model happy-path test) | NO_ENTRY — new discovery |\n\n---\n\n## Build Plan Summary\n\n**Order for Builder:**\n1. **T1 first** — commit + ship v12.1.1. Clears the working tree baseline before T3 touches runner.go again.\n2. **T2 second** — git rm --cached + .gitignore update. Fast (2 turns).\n3. **T3 last** — add resolver seam to runner.go + write happy-path test. Rebuild binary after (will need another v12.1.2 patch or roll into a batch).\n\n**Do not reorder T1 and T3:** runner.go in T3 must apply on top of the committed T1 change, not mixed with it.\n\n---\n\n## Decision Trace\n\n```json\n{\n  \"cycle\": 106,\n  \"mode\": \"full\",\n  \"goal\": null,\n  \"systemHealth\": {\n    \"lastCommitSHA\": \"05ee503\",\n    \"allTestsPass\": true,\n    \"bridgeCoverage\": \"97.8%\",\n    \"runnerCoverage\": \"100% statement (happy-path branch gap)\"\n  },\n  \"uncommittedChanges\": [\n    \"go/internal/adapters/bridge/bridge.go\",\n    \"go/internal/adapters/bridge/bridge_test.go\",\n    \"go/internal/phases/runner/runner.go\"\n  ],\n  \"selectedTasks\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"t1-ship-v12.1.1\",\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"weight\": \"S\",\n      \"effort\": 3,\n      \"targetFiles\": [\"bridge.go\", \"bridge_test.go\", \"runner.go\", \"go/evolve\"],\n      \"researchBacking\": \"git diff HEAD confirms changes; all tests green\",\n      \"recommendedSkills\": [\n        {\"name\": \"evolve-loop:evolve-ship\", \"priority\": \"primary\"},\n        {\"name\": \"go-build\", \"priority\": \"supplementary\"}\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"t2-untrack-artifacts\",\n      \"priority\": 2,\n      \"weight\": \"S\",\n      \"effort\": 2,\n      \"targetFiles\": [\".gitignore\"],\n      \"researchBacking\": \"git status shows tracked runtime logs; stale cycle-state.json blocked scout write\",\n      \"recommendedSkills\": [{\"name\": \"git-workflow\", \"priority\": \"primary\"}]\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"t3-auto-model-test\",\n      \"priority\": 3,\n      \"weight\": \"S\",\n      \"effort\": 3,\n      \"targetFiles\": [\"runner.go\", \"runner_test.go\"],\n      \"researchBacking\": \"resolvellm.Options.ConfigPath seam exists; happy-path branch uncovered\",\n      \"recommendedSkills\": [\n        {\"name\": \"go-review\", \"priority\": \"primary\"},\n        {\"name\": \"tdd\", \"priority\": \"supplementary\"}\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Reflection\n\n**What went well:** Parallel reads (mailbox + brief + cycle-state) and early diff check surfaced all three findings within 8 turns.\n\n**Friction:** Stale `go/.evolve/cycle-state.json` triggered role-gate enforcement against phantom cycle-1, blocking the first Write attempt. Cleaned by removing the artifact.\n\n```yaml\n# scout-reflection.yaml\nphase: scout\ncycle: 106\nfriction_points:\n  - type: stale-artifact\n    detail: \"go/.evolve/cycle-state.json (cycle-1) blocked Write to cycle-106 workspace via role-gate\"\nobservations:\n  - \"100% statement coverage masked branch gap — auto-model happy-path never exercised\"\n  - \"go/.evolve/ tracking root cause: binary CWD anchoring vs git-root anchoring\"\nverdict: on-track\nturns_used: 9\n```\n","numLines":257,"startLine":1,"totalLines":257}}}
