{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015GoEXcM9hS5d2ghSJuGjPX","type":"tool_result","content":"# Opt C cycle 1 (shadow) — wire build-planner phase between TDD and Build\n\n> **Spec for `/evolve-loop`.** Cycle 1 of 3 for Opt C from the parent plan `i-feel-the-whole-zany-sky.md`. Ships **wiring only**: persona, profile, phase-registry entry, dispatch + gate plumbing, orchestrator persona update. `EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER=0` default — the persona does NOT run on shipped cycles. Cycle 2 will flip the default to advisory; cycle 3 removes Builder's Step 3 and enforces `## Plan Adherence` checks. Acceptance-gate monitoring kicks in after cycle 3.\n\n## Context\n\nUser pain: Builder's median turn count is 39 vs target ≤25, and audit-FAIL rate is higher than the project's accuracy goal. Hypothesis: Builder's internal Step 3 (chain-of-thought design within the same LLM session) burns the turn budget on design work, leaving fewer turns for implementation, and produces low-quality predicate-to-directive mappings that the Auditor flags as defects. Externalizing design into a dedicated `build-planner` phase (Opus, separate session from Builder's Sonnet) should improve adherence without violating anti-cooperative-bias (TDD-Engineer Opus session A → build-planner Opus session B with disjoint context → Builder Sonnet session C → Auditor Opus session D).\n\nWhy it matters: this cycle is the foundation for the next 2 cycles. If the wiring is wrong (broken phase-registry entry, missing gate, persona dispatcher allowlist gap), cycle 2's flag flip would land an actively-broken pipeline. Shadow-wiring keeps the flag OFF so nothing changes at runtime; only the structural integrity is verified.\n\n## Hard constraints (do not violate)\n\n- `EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER` defaults to `0` after this cycle ships. No runtime change to existing cycles.\n- Anti-cooperative-bias: build-planner persona must be a separate LLM session from Builder. Even though both are Opus by default in the persona file, they MUST run via independent `subagent-run.sh` dispatches with disjoint contexts.\n- Trust kernel: build-planner is a normal subagent under `subagent-run.sh`, profile-restricted, ledger-recorded. No bypass.\n- Single-writer: `build-planner.json` declares `parallel_eligible: false` (single-writer for build-plan.md).\n- Cycle binding: build-planner captures `git_head` + `tree_state_sha` like every other phase.\n- Bash 3.2 compatibility throughout (per CLAUDE.md banned-patterns table).\n\n## Approved scope (10 files)\n\n### NEW files\n\n1. **`agents/evolve-build-planner.md`** — persona file:\n   - YAML frontmatter: `name: evolve-build-planner`, `description`, `model: opus`, `tools: Read, Grep, Glob, Write`, `perspective: planner`.\n   - Sections: Inputs, Pipeline Position, Workflow Steps 1-5, Turn budget, Shared Constraints.\n   - Inputs every cycle: `intent.md`, `scout-report.md`, `triage-decision.md`, `acs/cycle-N/*.sh` (TDD's predicates).\n   - Inputs on retry only: above + prior `audit-report.md` (FAIL verdict + defects) + prior `build-report.md`.\n   - Output: `build-plan.md` with mandatory sections `## Task sequencing`, `## Priority justification`, `## Implementation directives` (numbered, Builder must address each by name), `## Predicate-to-code map`, `## Risk assessment`. On retry: also `## Failure-class taxonomy`.\n   - Turn cap 10. Budget cap $0.30.\n\n2. **`.evolve/profiles/build-planner.json`** — profile:\n   - `name`, `role: build-planner`, `cli: claude`, `model_tier_default: opus`.\n   - `allowed_tools`: `Read`, `Grep`, `Glob`, `Write(.evolve/runs/cycle-*/build-plan.md)`.\n   - `disallowed_tools`: full Edit-denial set (mirror `.evolve/profiles/tester.json:disallowed_tools`).\n   - `sandbox`: `enabled: true`, `read_only_repo: true`, `write_subpaths: [\".evolve/runs/cycle-*\"]`.\n   - `parallel_eligible: false`. `max_turns: 10`. `max_budget_usd: 0.30`. `challenge_token_required: true`.\n   - `output_artifact: \".evolve/runs/cycle-{cycle}/build-plan.md\"`.\n\n3. **`docs/architecture/adr/0019-build-planner-phase.md`** — Architecture Decision Record:\n   - Records the v10.19 decision: plan-mode externalized between TDD and Build.\n   - Documents the 3-cycle rollout (shadow → advisory → enforce).\n   - Documents the acceptance gates (turn-count ≤25, FAIL-rate ≥20% reduction).\n   - Lists the revert path (`EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER=0`).\n\n### EDIT files\n\n4. **`docs/architecture/phase-registry.json`** — insert build-planner phase between `tdd` (index 4) and `build` (index 5):\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"name\": \"build-planner\",\n     \"role\": \"build-planner\",\n     \"optional\": true,\n     \"enable_var\": \"EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER\",\n     \"inputs\": {\n       \"files\": [\n         \".evolve/runs/cycle-{cycle}/intent.md\",\n         \".evolve/runs/cycle-{cycle}/scout-report.md\",\n         \".evolve/runs/cycle-{cycle}/triage-decision.md\",\n         \".evolve/runs/cycle-{cycle}/tdd-contract.md\"\n       ],\n       \"state_fields\": []\n     },\n     \"outputs\": {\n       \"files\": [\".evolve/runs/cycle-{cycle}/build-plan.md\"]\n     },\n     \"gate_in\": \"gate_tdd_to_build_planner\",\n     \"gate_out\": \"gate_build_planner_to_build\",\n     \"parallel_eligible\": false,\n     \"skippable_when_present\": false\n   }\n   ```\n   Also update `tdd.gate_out` from `gate_discover_to_build` to `gate_tdd_to_build_planner`.\n\n5. **`scripts/dispatch/list-phase-order.sh`** — insert `build-planner` between `tdd` and `build` in `emit_hardcoded_order()` (line 38-39).\n\n6. **`scripts/dispatch/subagent-run.sh`** — add `build-planner` to two allowlist regexes:\n   - Line 631 (cmd_run agent_role allowlist)\n   - Line 1454 (cmd_dispatch_parallel agent allowlist)\n\n7. **`scripts/guards/phase-gate-precondition.sh`** — add `build-planner` to the recognized-agents case statement (line 166) AND to the worker-pattern alternation (line 169) for `build-planner-worker-*` if applicable.\n\n8. **`scripts/lifecycle/phase-gate.sh`** — add two new gate functions:\n   - `gate_tdd_to_build_planner` — verifies `tdd-contract.md` (or whatever the TDD output file is named in this codebase) exists, is fresh, has substantive content. Verifies a tdd-engineer ledger entry exists.\n   - `gate_build_planner_to_build` — verifies `build-plan.md` exists with all 5 mandatory section headings (`## Task sequencing`, `## Priority justification`, `## Implementation directives`, `## Predicate-to-code map`, `## Risk assessment`). On retry, also verify `## Failure-class taxonomy`.\n   Wire both into the GATE-dispatching switch at the bottom of phase-gate.sh.\n\n9. **`agents/evolve-orchestrator-reference.md`** — insert a conditional build-planner step between the existing TDD step and the Build step. Pattern: `if [ \"${EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER:-0}\" = \"1\" ]; then; cycle-state.sh advance build-planner build-planner; subagent-run.sh build-planner $CYCLE $WORKSPACE; fi`.\n\n10. **`docs/architecture/control-flags.md`** — add row for `EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER`: `ACTIVE (wired v10.19; default off)`. Description: \"Opt C: run build-planner phase between TDD and Build. Default 0 (shadow ship; persona not invoked). Flipped to 1 in v10.20 (advisory); Builder Step 3 removed in v10.21 (enforce).\"\n    Plus `CLAUDE.md` env-var table row mirroring the same.\n\n### Test files\n\n11. **EXTEND `scripts/tests/phase-gate-precondition-test.sh`** — add tests:\n    - `phase=tdd + build-planner → ALLOW` (next phase)\n    - `phase=tdd + build → DENY when EVOLVE_BUILD_PLANNER=1` (must go through build-planner first) — note: this test may need to be deferred to cycle 2 if the guard doesn't read the env var\n\n12. **NEW `scripts/tests/build-planner-wire-test.sh`** — verifies:\n    - `agents/evolve-build-planner.md` exists with valid YAML frontmatter","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"715c7e05-5ffe-4c3b-8250-1e3ef685eb10","uuid":"40ffe029-5a56-4493-858a-3fcbc312db2c","timestamp":"2026-05-25T06:40:08.062Z","tool_